<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>An man attending a demonstration in Rochester was struck by a car, and police in Pittsburgh launched an investigation after protesters clashed with civilians over this week.</p>

<p>In the United States, Labor Day Weekend included a number of anti-racism protests across the nation that continued to fight against racial inequality and police brutality.</p>

<p>Social media has been flooded with a mix of footage showing peaceful protests, chaotic clashes with law enforcement and heavily-armed demonstrators from both sides of the political spectrum. </p>

<p>The demonstrations have been in response to several black Americans who have died in police custody, with the death of Daniel Prude in March sparking the most recent wave of outrage.</p>

<p>On Friday, an unidentified man who among protesters at one such rally in Rochester, New York, was struck by a vehicle in shocking footage.</p>

<p>Shared by Carolyn Delvecchio Hoffman to Storyful, the minute-long footage shows a group of demonstrators standing in an intersection during the city's third night of protest. </p>

<p>Protesters watch a vehicle turning right out of the intersection with a screech, but a few voices suddenly scream out in warning.</p>

<p>Seconds later, a red vehicle accelerates into the crowd and the driver unleashes a wave of yellow spray paint at protesters.  </p>

